   {:e #blake3 "c1ee3af8ec170ff90deb303c4fc8977ef90d77cf56367ed5cb61f2821e82fd52" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Resolution module (1,341 LOC) has 23 unit tests but lacks property-based tests for commutativity and idempotence. These are the algebraic properties that guarantee CRDT merge correctness. RATIONALE: INV-RESOLUTION-001 (commutativity), INV-RESOLUTION-002 (determinism). Stateright tests verify merge-level CRDT properties, but NOT resolution-function-level properties with arbitrary inputs. A single counterexample could corrupt all future merges. APPROACH: PROPTEST: (1) Generate random attribute with random resolution mode (LWW, Lattice, MultiValue). (2) Generate two conflicting values. (3) Verify: resolve(v1, v2) == resolve(v2, v1) for ALL modes (commutativity). (4) Verify: resolve(resolve(a, b), b) == resolve(a, b) (idempotence). (5) Verify for Lattice mode: resolve(resolve(a, b), c) == resolve(a, resolve(b, c)) (associativity). (6) 1000 cases per property. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: On counterexample, log: mode, value_a, value_b, resolve(a,b), resolve(b,a), expected equality. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/resolution.rs (add proptest module)" :op :assert}
